  "text": "The complaints at admission are non-specific in most of the patients such as menstrual irregularities, pelvic pain, palpable pelvic mass and menorrhagia. The tumors may present with postmenopausal bleeding in older patients, and puberte precox in children (2) [CITATION_1] (4) .",
